## 3. SaaS Admin Dashboard (Super Admin)

The Super Admin panel is operated by the **Netra Analytics platform team** to manage all tenants, billing, infrastructure, and system health.

### 3.1 Tenant & Account Management
- **All Tenants List** — Searchable, filterable table of all registered organizations
- **Tenant Profile** — View workspace details, owner, plan, usage stats, creation date
- **Impersonate Tenant** — Securely log in as any tenant for support (with audit trail)
- **Suspend / Reactivate Account** — Disable tenant access while preserving data
- **Delete Tenant** — Soft-delete with 30-day recovery window, hard-delete scheduler
- **Merge Accounts** — Merge duplicate or trial → paid accounts

### 3.2 Subscription & Billing Management
- **Plan Assignment** — Manually assign or override subscription tiers
- **Billing History** — View all invoices per tenant
- **Revenue Dashboard** — MRR, ARR, churn rate, new signups, plan distribution charts
- **Coupon & Promo Code Management** — Create, assign, and track discount codes
- **Trial Extension** — Extend trial period for specific tenants
- **Stripe Integration View** — Link to Stripe customer record per tenant

### 3.3 Platform Usage & Quotas
- **Event Volume Monitor** — Real-time and historical event ingestion rates per tenant
- **Storage Usage** — ClickHouse data size per tenant
- **API Rate Limits** — Configure and enforce per-tenant ingestion rate limits
- **Quota Alerts** — Auto-notify tenants approaching plan limits
- **Throttling Controls** — Temporarily throttle high-volume tenants

### 3.4 User & Roles Management
- **All Users List** — Cross-tenant user directory
- **Role Assignment** — Super Admin, Admin, Analyst, Viewer roles
- **Team Management** — View all members of any workspace
- **Audit Log** — Full trail of all admin actions (who did what, when)

### 3.5 Data Pipeline Health
- **Kafka Cluster Monitor** — Consumer lag, topic throughput, broker health
- **ClickHouse Health** — Query latency, disk usage, replication status
- **Ingestion Error Log** — Failed event payloads with tenant context and error reason
- **Data Retention Policies** — Configure per-plan data retention windows (30/90/365 days)
- **Backfill Jobs** — Trigger historical data re-processing jobs

### 3.6 SDK & Plugin Registry
- **SDK Version Manager** — Track which tenants are on which SDK version
- **Plugin / SDK Release Manager** — Publish new SDK releases with changelogs
- **Deprecation Alerts** — Notify tenants using outdated SDK versions

### 3.7 System Configuration
- **Feature Flags** — Toggle beta features per tenant or globally
- **Email Template Manager** — Edit transactional email templates
- **Announcement Banner** — Push system-wide banners to user dashboards
- **Maintenance Mode** — Enable/disable maintenance windows

### 3.8 Analytics & Reporting (Platform Meta-Analytics)
- **Signup Funnel Analytics** — Conversion from visit → trial → paid
- **Platform Adoption Heatmap** — Which of the 9 SDK platforms are most used
- **Feature Usage Stats** — Which dashboard features are used most
- **Support Ticket Volume** — Integrated with helpdesk (e.g., Intercom/Crisp)

