## 7. System Architecture Diagrams

### 7.1 High-Level System Architecture

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph CLIENTS["📱 Client Endpoints (9 Platforms)"]
        WP[WordPress / WooCommerce<br/>PHP Plugin]
        MAG[Magento 2<br/>PHP Extension]
        PS[PrestaShop<br/>PHP Module]
        SHO[Shopify<br/>Node.js App]
        WEB[Web JS<br/>Autocapture Script]
        RN[React Native<br/>TypeScript SDK]
        AND[Android Native<br/>Kotlin SDK]
        IOS[iOS Native<br/>Swift SDK]
        UNI[Unity<br/>C# SDK]
    end

    subgraph INGESTION["⚡ Stateless Ingestion Layer"]
        ING[Fastify Ingestion API<br/>Node.js / TypeScript]
        REDIS[(Redis Cache<br/>API Key Validation)]
        GEO[MaxMind GeoIP<br/>Resolution]
        PII[PII Sanitizer<br/>SHA-256 Hashing]
    end

    subgraph PIPELINE["🔄 Data Pipeline"]
        KAFKA[Apache Kafka<br/>Event Stream Broker]
        CH_KAFKA[ClickHouse Kafka Engine<br/>Stream Consumer]
    end

    subgraph STORAGE["🗄️ Storage Layer"]
        CH[(ClickHouse Cluster<br/>OLAP - Events)]
        PG[(PostgreSQL<br/>OLTP - Users/Billing)]
        MINIO[(MinIO<br/>S3 - Files/Reports)]
    end

    subgraph BACKEND["🖥️ Application Backend"]
        NEXT[Next.js API Routes<br/>App Layer]
        BULLMQ[BullMQ<br/>Job Queue]
        SOCKET[Socket.io<br/>WebSocket Server]
    end

    subgraph FRONTEND["🌐 Frontend"]
        STORE[Next.js Storefront<br/>SSG/SSR - Marketing]
        DASH[React Dashboard<br/>Analytics UI]
        TAGGER[Visual Event Tagger<br/>Iframe + PostMessage]
    end

    CLIENTS -->|JSON HTTP POST| ING
    ING <-->|Validate Key| REDIS
    ING --> PII
    ING --> GEO
    ING -->|Publish Event| KAFKA
    KAFKA --> CH_KAFKA
    CH_KAFKA -->|Batch Insert| CH

    NEXT <-->|SQL Queries| CH
    NEXT <-->|CRUD Queries| PG
    NEXT --> BULLMQ
    BULLMQ --> MINIO

    SOCKET -->|Realtime Push| DASH
    NEXT --> SOCKET

    DASH <-->|REST / WS| NEXT
    STORE <-->|REST| NEXT
```

---

### 7.2 Event Data Flow (Detailed)

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant CLIENT as Client SDK<br/>(any platform)
    participant API as Ingestion API<br/>(Fastify)
    participant CACHE as Redis Cache
    participant KAFKA as Apache Kafka
    participant CH as ClickHouse
    participant DASH as Analytics Dashboard

    CLIENT->>API: POST /ingest (JSON Event Payload)
    API->>CACHE: Validate tenant_id & API key
    CACHE-->>API: Valid / Rate limit status
    API->>API: Strip PII, Resolve GeoIP, Add server timestamp
    API->>KAFKA: Produce to topic "raw_events"
    API-->>CLIENT: 200 OK (immediate response)

    Note over KAFKA,CH: Asynchronous Batch Processing
    KAFKA->>CH: Kafka Engine consumes micro-batches
    CH->>CH: Insert into events_local MergeTree table
    CH->>CH: Materialized Views compute rollups

    DASH->>API: GET /api/dashboard/pageviews?range=7d
    API->>CH: SELECT ... FROM events WHERE tenant_id=X AND date>=...
    CH-->>API: Aggregated result set (ms latency)
    API-->>DASH: JSON metrics response
```

---

### 7.3 Multi-Tenant Database Architecture

```mermaid
graph LR
    subgraph PG["PostgreSQL (OLTP)"]
        direction TB
        T1[tenants table<br/>id, name, plan, stripe_id]
        T2[users table<br/>id, tenant_id, role, email]
        T3[projects table<br/>id, tenant_id, name, api_key]
        T4[tracking_rules table<br/>id, project_id, selector, event_name]
        T5[subscriptions table<br/>id, tenant_id, status, plan]
    end

    subgraph CH["ClickHouse (OLAP) — Shared Schema"]
        direction TB
        E1["events_local MergeTree<br/>ORDER BY (tenant_id, event_name, timestamp)"]
        E2["sessions MergeTree<br/>ORDER BY (tenant_id, session_id)"]
        E3["daily_rollups MaterializedView<br/>Pre-aggregated by tenant per day"]
        E4["hourly_rollups MaterializedView<br/>Pre-aggregated by tenant per hour"]
    end

    subgraph ISOLATION["Row-Level Security"]
        RLS[ClickHouse RLS Policy<br/>WHERE tenant_id = current_user_tenant]
    end

    T1 --- T2
    T1 --- T3
    T3 --- T4
    T1 --- T5

    E1 --> E3
    E1 --> E4
    E1 --- RLS
    E2 --- RLS
```

---

### 7.4 No-Code Visual Event Tagger Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant USER as Non-Technical<br/>User (Marketer)
    participant DASH as Netra Dashboard
    participant IFRAME as User's Website<br/>(inside iframe)
    participant SDK as Tracking Script<br/>(on user's site)
    participant DB as Database

    USER->>DASH: Opens Visual Tagger tool
    DASH->>IFRAME: Load user's website in <iframe>
    DASH->>SDK: postMessage: "ENTER_TAGGING_MODE"
    SDK->>IFRAME: Inject transparent DOM overlay
    SDK->>IFRAME: Register mousemove → highlight element

    USER->>IFRAME: Hovers over "Buy Now" button
    IFRAME-->>USER: Highlighted with colored border

    USER->>IFRAME: Clicks "Buy Now" button
    SDK->>DASH: postMessage: { selector: "#buy-btn", elementText: "Buy Now" }
    DASH-->>USER: Show "Name this event" dialog
    USER->>DASH: Types "Purchase_Initiated" → Save

    DASH->>DB: Store { selector: "#buy-btn", event_name: "Purchase_Initiated" }
    DB-->>DASH: Rule saved ✓
    DASH->>SDK: postMessage: "SYNC_TRACKING_RULES"

    Note over SDK,DB: In Production Runtime
    SDK->>SDK: User clicks #buy-btn on live site
    SDK->>SDK: Match selector against cached rules
    SDK->>API: POST /ingest { event_name: "Purchase_Initiated" }
```

